 Lvovich and I knew him and his first wife, Svetlana Chertok, the pianist, very intimately. He was interned by the Nazis separately from Mira, and died in the same concentration camp as did my elder brother Misha. You did not know Misha, did you? He was also in love with Mira once upon a time.”

“Tshay gotoff (tea’s ready),” called Susan from the porch in her funny functional Russian. “Timofey, Rozochka! Tshay!”

